The T stage is determined by the size of the primary tumor.
T1 is further divided into T1a, T1b, and T1c based on the tumor size.
T1a: 0.55 cm or less
T1b: More than 0.55 cm but not more than 1 cm
T1c: More than 1 cm but not more than 2 cm
